In Eclipse, include all libraries by hand (as opposed to inserting "pkg-config..." as a build parameter).
This way, you get rid of eclipse parser errors and gain, among other things, autocompletion support.
Don't forget Project->Index->Rebuild

Include path for OpenCV Version 2.3.1:
	• pkg-config opencv --cflags
e.g. 
	/usr/include/opencv


Include paths for gtkmm: 
	• pkg-config gtkmm-2.4 --cflags
e.g.
	/usr/include/gtk-2.0
	/usr/include/gtk-unix-print-2.0
	/usr/include/atk-1.0
	/usr/include/glib-2.0
	/usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/glib-2.0/include
	/usr/include/pango-1.0
	/usr/include/cairo
	/usr/include/pixman-1
	/usr/include/freetype2
	/usr/include/libpng12
	/usr/lib/i386-linux-gnu/gtk-2.0/include
	/usr/include/gdk-pixbuf-2.0
	/usr/include/gio-unix-2.0/
	/usr/include/gtkmm-2.4
	/usr/lib/gtkmm-2.4/include
	/usr/include/atkmm-1.6
	/usr/include/giomm-2.4
	/usr/include/pangomm-1.4
	/usr/lib/pangomm-1.4/include
	/usr/include/gdkmm-2.4
	/usr/lib/gdkmm-2.4/include
	/usr/include/glibmm-2.4
	/usr/lib/glibmm-2.4/include
	/usr/include/sigc++-2.0
	/usr/lib/sigc++-2.0/include
	/usr/include/cairomm-1.0
	/usr/lib/cairomm-1.0/include


Libraries to link for OpenCV Version 2.3.1:
	• pkg-config opencv --libs
e.g. 
	opencv_core
	opencv_imgproc 
	opencv_highgui 
	opencv_ml 
	opencv_video 
	opencv_features2d 
	opencv_calib3d 
	opencv_objdetect 
	opencv_contrib 
	opencv_legacy 
	opencv_flann


Libraries to link for gtkmm:
	• pkg-config gtkmm-2.4 --libs
e.g.
	gtkmm-2.4
	atkmm-1.6
	gdkmm-2.4
	giomm-2.4
	pangomm-1.4
	gtk-x11-2.0
	glibmm-2.4
	cairomm-1.0
	sigc-2.0
	gdk-x11-2.0
	atk-1.0
	gio-2.0
	pangoft2-1.0
	pangocairo-1.0
	gdk_pixbuf-2.0
	cairo
	pango-1.0
	freetype
	fontconfig
	gobject-2.0
	gmodule-2.0
	gthread-2.0
	rt
	glib-2.0



